modules.description: This module defines a connection configuration for Azure Blob Storage, including account key, name, protocol, and suffix. It provides functions to parse a connection string into this configuration, compare configurations for equality, and serialize or deserialize them using S-expressions. A typical use case involves initializing or parsing a connection string to interact with Azure Blob Storage services.

This module constructs URIs and signs request headers for Azure Blob Storage API operations, handling connections, paths, query parameters, HTTP methods, and headers. It supports generating signed URLs for blob access and preparing authenticated HTTP requests. The child module manages connection configurations, including account key, name, protocol, and suffix, with functions to parse, compare, and serialize them. Together, they enable secure, programmatic interaction with blob storage, such as uploading files, generating time-limited access links, and managing container metadata.
